  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has issued an email alert, however the most significant development is the Belgian regulator FSMA flagging 6 unauthorized crypto providers after the MiCA deadline, highlighting the importance of compliance with the new EU regulation. The Dutch central bank has also imposed a $12.5 million fine on ABN Amro for inadequate anti-money laundering safeguards, demonstrating the ongoing focus on financial crime prevention. Meanwhile, ESMA has published technical standards on CCP admission criteria and guidelines on MiCA stablecoin, further clarifying the regulatory framework for the EU financial sector. The FSMA's action against unauthorized crypto providers is particularly notable as it is a direct enforcement of the MiCA regulation in Belgium.",
